    "entity_count": 120,
    "description": "Curated EUKARYOTE contaminant-anchor roster x spliced CDS GCF_028828025.1 ASM2882802v1 (NCBI, public domain). 11 representative loci (NOT genome-complete \u2014 a ~32 Mb / ~13k-gene mold): the conidiation / airborne-spore cascade (fluG/flbA, brlA->abaA->wetA, a rodlet spore-wall hydrophobin) + the pksP conidial-pigment PKS + the penicillin-biosynthesis cluster (pcbC isopenicillin-N synthase, penDE acyltransferase \u2014 the penicillin origin story + chemical warfare vs. bacteria) + saprotroph housekeeping (gpdA, niaD nitrate assimilation). P. rubens (chrysogenum) Wisconsin 54-1255: 32.19 Mb / 12,943 genes; the single most common mold genus in indoor + outdoor air, and the penicillin origin organism. The immigration kernel reads role + trait levers, not specific genes (ADR-019 S0, Mode A contaminant).",
